						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the wall (inner side), left of entrance into the central shrine of the Śaṅkarliṅga temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Bhillama—A.D. 1187.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated in the king's regnal <hi rend="bold">year 3, Plavaṅga, Bhādrapada, Amāvāsyā, solar eclipse,</hi> probably corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1187, September 4,</hi> which was a <hi rend="bold">Friday.</hi> There was a solar eclipse on that day but the <hi rend="italic">Kanyā-saṅkramaṇa</hi> had occurred on the previous Friday.</p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of land and toll-income by Māyidēva and others to Kōṭiśaṁkaradēva of <hi rend="bold">Nimbahura.</hi> Other gifts of money and lands in different villages (specified) made by Gaṁgara Kanniseṭṭi and others, for the benefit of the same temple, are also recorded.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. XXVIII, pp. 94 ff.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
